text.tspan: On the main menu (the first one), we could include descriptions
We even could discard the "circle" idea, and go like:
The point of a QGV is that we can do smooth and nice effects.
So, when you click on an item, a similar QGV is shown
but with the details of that item you selected.
When we really reach the moment to show the configure widget itself,
QGV wont represent a problem. We will have a layout with:
+ QGV showing something (the title and information of what you
are configuring, or something, but really smooth).
+ The widget itself, as a normal widget.
